{"lemma":"أُسْبُوعِ","slug":"أُسْبُوعِ","root":"س.ب.ع","root_slug":"س-ب-ع","root_link":"/words/roots/س-ب-ع","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n18764"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8F%D8%B3%D9%92%D8%A8%D9%8F%D9%88%D8%B9%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"week (unit of time)"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Compare with Hebrew שבוע (šavúaʿ, “week”) and Classical Syriac ܫܒܘܥܐ (šaḇoʿā, “week”)."},"ipa":["/ʔus.buːʕ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n18764","headword_ar":"اُسْبُوعٌ","root":"sbE","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain number of days;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * Msb, K; *) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"seven days; a week;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb;) also termed ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"subuwEN","text_ar":"سُبُوعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Lth, Msb, K,) by some of the Arabs; (Lth, Msb;) [and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suboEN","text_ar":"سُبْعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", as shown by what follows:] pl. of the first"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asaAbiyEu","text_ar":"اَسَابِيعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb, TA.) One says, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aqamotu Einodahu suboEayoni","text_ar":"اَقَمْتُ عِنْدَهُ سُبْعَيْنِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^usobuwEayoni","text_ar":"اُسْبُوعَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is more common,] i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I remained at his abode two weeks."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-  Also The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"seventh day;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"subuwEN","text_ar":"سُبُوعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; as in a trad., where it is said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_i*aA kaAna yawoma subuwEihi","text_ar":"اـِذَا كَانَ يَوْمَ سُبُوعِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"When his seventh day after the celebration of his marriage is come."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) [↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yawomu Als~ubuwEi","text_ar":"يَوْمُ السُّبُوعِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used in this sense in the present day: and also as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The seventh day after childbirth;"},{"kind":"text","text":"in which sense it is generally to be understood when used unrestrictedly; as this day is celebrated with more rejoicing than the former: also as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the seventh day after the return from pilgrimage."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Seven circuitings"},{"kind":"text","text":"[round the House of God, meaning the Kaabeh]: (Lth, Mgh, Msb:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asaAbiyEu","text_ar":"اَسَابِيعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^usobuwEaAtN","text_ar":"اُسْبُوعَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Lth, Mgh, Msb.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAfa biAlbayoti A^usobuwEFA","text_ar":"طَافَ بِالبَيْتِ اُسْبُوعًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, * K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"subuwEFA","text_ar":"سُبُوعًا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Lth, IDrd, K,) but A boo Sa'eed says, I know not any one who has said this except IDrd, and the former is the word commonly known, (TA,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saboEFA","text_ar":"سَبْعًا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suboEFA","text_ar":"سُبْعًا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He circuited round the House"},{"kind":"text","text":"[of God]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"seven times,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"seven circuitings;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"valaAvapa A^asaAbiyEa","text_ar":"ثَلَاثَةَ اَسَابِيعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thrice seven times,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thrice seven circuitings"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.)"}],"source_refs":["Lth","Msb","K","Mgh","S","IDrd","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}